$ Using Oracle Data Cartridge Interface for User Defined Aggragation Functions

With Data Cartridges, it is possible to create user defined → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/select/aggregate[aggregate functions].

{ Example

  { Specification of a type with the required interface

    gh|Oracle-patterns|/misc/ODCI/aggregation/ex-01/type.sql||

  }
  { Implementation of the type

    gh|Oracle-patterns|/misc/ODCI/aggregation/ex-01/type-body.sql||

  }
  { The user defined function

    gh|Oracle-patterns|/misc/ODCI/aggregation/ex-01/func.sql||

  }
  { Test table and data

    gh|Oracle-patterns|/misc/ODCI/aggregation/ex-01/test-table.sql||

  }
  { Using the function in a select statement

    gh|Oracle-patterns|/misc/ODCI/aggregation/ex-01/test-select.sql||

  }
  { Cleaning up 

    gh|Oracle-patterns|/misc/ODCI/aggregation/ex-01/clean-up.sql||

  }

}

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/Data-Cartridge: the → development/databases/Oracle/Data-Cartridge/interfaces#odci-intf-aggr[interface functions] for user defined functions.
